# Finote - Financial Management Application

## Project Overview
Finote is a comprehensive income and expense tracking web application built with Next.js 15, TypeScript, and TailwindCSS. The application supports both Thai and English languages with full internationalization.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS v4
- **Package Manager**: pnpm
- **Internationalization**: next-intl
- **Charts**: Recharts
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Data Persistence**: Browser localStorage

## Key Features
- Transaction management (CRUD operations)
- Budget tracking with visual progress indicators
- Financial goal setting and progress tracking
- Advanced analytics and insights
- Interactive charts and visualizations
- Multi-language support (Thai/English)
- Currency switching (THB/USD)
- Category management with color coding
- Toast notification system
- Demo data generation
- CSV export functionality

## Project Structure
- [src/app/[locale]/](mdc:src/app/[locale]/) - Main application pages with locale routing
- [src/components/](mdc:src/components/) - Reusable UI components
- [src/hooks/](mdc:src/hooks/) - Custom React hooks
- [src/types/](mdc:src/types/) - TypeScript type definitions
- [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils/) - Utility functions
- [messages/](mdc:messages/) - Translation files (th.json, en.json)
- [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts) - Next.js middleware for i18n
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration

## Development Guidelines
- Always use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow the established component structure
- Maintain internationalization support for all new features
- Use the toast notification system for user feedback
- Implement responsive design with TailwindCSS
- Follow the established naming conventions
